\b \cf0 Story Pages
\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Pages are represented by text documents in the \'93Draft 1\'94 folder. Upon compile for export or print, a page break is inserted between them.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li1440\fi-1440\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Note that the \'93Draft 1\'94 folder is what we refer to in the documentation as the \'93Draft folder\'94. A number has been appended for use in headers during Compile - see below.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Each \'93Page\'94 can contain numerous panels, followed by the description text and dialogue for that panel.\
{\listtext	\'95	}To create new pages, one way is to go to the Projects menu and select New From Template 
\f3 >
\f1  Comic Page. The new, blank page will appear immediately below the current Binder selection. You can also click and hold the green \'93Add\'94 toolbar button to select the \'93Comic Page\'94 document type, or hit Shift-Opt-Cmd-N on the keyboard. However, the easiest way is to click \'93Add\'94 or hit Cmd-N - while the focus is in the \'93Comic Script\'94 folder, new documents created will automatically be based on the \'93Comic Page\'94 template (which can be found in the \'93Templates\'94 folder). This is because the \'93Comic Script\'94 folder is set to use the \'93Comic Page\'94 template as its default document type (this has been set via Documents > Default Template for Subdocuments).\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0

